    "As showned in Figure 5 USAGE OF CODESWe use CodeS by fine-tuning and few-shot in-context learning.",
    "Formally, given training set 𝐷 = {𝑑 1, 𝑑2,..., 𝑑 ℎ } with ℎ text-to-SQL samples, each sample is a triplet (𝑑 𝑑𝑏 𝑖, 𝑑 𝑞 𝑖, 𝑑 𝑠𝑞𝑙 𝑖) denoting the database, question, and associated SQL query.",
    "For a test sample 𝑡, consisting of database 𝑡 𝑑𝑏 and question 𝑡 𝑞, we aim to generate SQL query 𝑡 𝑠𝑞𝑙.",
    "Before employing CodeS, we first convert each database in the text-to-SQL sample into its corresponding database prompt (see Section 6).",
    "Thus, each training sample is represented as a triplet: (𝑑 𝑑𝑏𝑝 𝑖, 𝑑 𝑞 𝑖, 𝑑 𝑠𝑞𝑙 𝑖), with 𝑑 𝑑𝑏𝑝 𝑖being the prompt for database 𝑑 𝑑𝑏 𝑖."
